@startuml 05-bounded-context-map
title HexaStock — DDD Bounded Context Map

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ArrowColor #1f4e79
skinparam Component {
  BorderColor #1f4e79
  BackgroundColor #fff3cd
}

rectangle "Portfolio Management\n(Portfolio, Lot, Transaction)" as portfolios
rectangle "Market Data\n(Ticker, StockPrice)" as marketdata
rectangle "Watchlists / Market Sentinel\n(Watchlist, AlertEntry)" as watchlists
rectangle "Notifications\n(NotificationChannel,\nDestination, Sender)" as notifications

portfolios     -> marketdata    : Customer / Supplier\n(MarketDataPort, Ticker)
watchlists     -> marketdata    : Customer / Supplier\n(MarketDataPort, Ticker)
watchlists     -> notifications : Published Language\n(WatchlistAlertTriggeredEvent)
notifications  -> marketdata    : Conformist\n(reuses Ticker VO)

note bottom of marketdata
  Shared kernel candidate:
  Ticker, StockPrice, Money are
  consumed by every BC.
end note

note right of watchlists
  Publishes domain events,
  knows nothing about who
  consumes them.
end note

note left of notifications
  Anti-corruption layer absent
  by design: today the upstream
  event vocabulary is small and
  stable enough to consume directly.
end note

legend bottom right
  Relationship vocabulary follows
  Eric Evans / Vaughn Vernon
  Context Mapping conventions.
endlegend

@enduml
